The relative '''strength''' of two systems of [[formal logic]] can be defined via [[model theory]]. Specifically, a logic <math>\alpha</math> is said to be as strong as a logic <math>\beta</math> if every [[elementary class]] in <math>\beta</math> is an elementary class in <math>\alpha</math>.<ref>[[Heinz-Dieter Ebbinghaus]] ''Extended logics: the general framework'' in [[Jon Barwise|K. J. Barwise]] and [[Solomon Feferman|S. Feferman]], editors, ''Model-theoretic logics'', 1985 {{isbn|0-387-90936-2}} page 43</ref>
